xxl.core.comparators

Class FeatureComparator<S,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.comparators.FeatureComparator<S,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of the objects the underlying comparator is able to compare.
    T - the type of the objects this comparator should be able to compare.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparator<T>

    public class FeatureComparator<S,T>
extends Object
implements Comparator<T>, Serializable
    The FeatureComparator compares the 'feature's of two given objects. The feature of each object is extracted with a mapping function, i.e., this classs implements the compare method as follows: 
       public int compare(T o1, T o2) {
       return comparator.compare(function1.invoke(o1), function2.invoke(o2));
   }

    If the two objects are of the same type it is more convenient to use hand over only one mapping function.

    See Also:
    Comparator, Function, Serialized Form
